The Stars that weave the night  
Remind us of the blight  
And Fortune's mask upon our Hearts  
- Just tenderly, the Sighs -  

To flow with cherished Dreams around -  
And every cloud that falls -  
In Nature's reign, a solace found  
Brings peace to every Call -  


- Emily Dickinson
